{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id05c265bd-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2292"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2292"},"text":"§ 2292.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Weekly amounts","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id05c265be-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2292/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Formula","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Subject to subsections (b) and (c), the trade readjustment allowance payable to an adversely affected worker for a week of total unemployment shall be an amount equal to the most recent weekly benefit amount of the unemployment insurance payable to the worker for a week of total unemployment preceding the worker’s first exhaustion of unemployment insurance (as determined for purposes of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s2291/a/3/B"},"text":"section 2291(a)(3)(B) of this title","children":[],"tail":") reduced (but not below zero) by—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id05c265bf-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2292/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any training allowance deductible under subsection (c); and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id05c265c0-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2292/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" income that is deductible from unemployment insurance under the disqualifying income provisions of the applicable State law or Federal unemployment insurance law.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id05c265c1-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2292/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Adversely affected workers who are undergoing training","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Any adversely affected worker who is entitled to trade readjustment allowances and who is undergoing training approved by the Secretary shall receive for each week in which he is undergoing any such training, a trade readjustment allowance in an amount (computed for such week) equal to the amount computed under subsection (a) or (if greater) the amount of any weekly allowance for such training to which he would be entitled under any other Federal law for the training of workers, if he applied for such allowance. Such trade readjustment allowance shall be paid in lieu of any training allowance to which the worker would be entitled under such other Federal law.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id05c265c2-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2292/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Deduction from total number of weeks of allowance entitlement","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"If a training allowance under any Federal law other than this chapter is paid to an adversely affected worker for any week of unemployment with respect to which he would be entitled (determined without regard to any disqualification under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s2291/b"},"text":"section 2291(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":") to a trade readjustment allowance if he applied for such allowance, each such week shall be deducted from the total number of weeks of trade readjustment allowance otherwise payable to him under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s2293/a"},"text":"section 2293(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":" when he applies for a trade readjustment allowance and is determined to be entitled to such allowance. If such training allowance paid to such worker for any week of unemployment is less than the amount of the trade readjustment allowance to which he would be entitled if he applied for such allowance, he shall receive, when he applies for a trade readjustment allowance and is determined to be entitled to such allowance, a trade readjustment allowance for such week equal to such difference."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id05c265c3-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/618/tII/s232"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–618, title II, § 232","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-01-03"},"text":"Jan. 3, 1975","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/2021"},"text":"88 Stat. 2021","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/35/tXXV/s2504/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–35, title XXV, § 2504(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-08-13"},"text":"Aug. 13, 1981","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/95/883"},"text":"95 Stat. 883","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/272/tXIII/s13003/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–272, title XIII, § 13003(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-04-07"},"text":"Apr. 7, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/301"},"text":"100 Stat. 301","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/418/tI/s1423/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–418, title I, § 1423(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-08-23"},"text":"Aug. 23, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/1246"},"text":"102 Stat. 1246","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/5/dB/tI/s1822"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–5, div. B, title I, § 1822","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-02-17"},"text":"Feb. 17, 2009","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/123/377"},"text":"123 Stat. 377","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/40/tII/s201/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–40, title II, § 201(b)","children":[],"tail":", (c), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 2011","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/125/403"},"text":"125 Stat. 403","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/27/tIV/s402/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–27, title IV, § 402(b)","children":[],"tail":", (c), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2015-06-29"},"text":"June 29, 2015","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/129/374"},"text":"129 Stat. 374","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id05c265c4-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"prospectiveAmendment","id":"id05c265c5-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Termination of Assistance","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For termination of assistance under this part after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-06-30"},"text":"June 30, 2022","children":[],"tail":", see Termination Date note below."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id05c265c6-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id05c265c7-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in subsec. (c), was in the original “this Act”, meaning ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/618"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–618","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-01-03"},"text":"Jan. 3, 1975","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/1978"},"text":"88 Stat. 1978","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to this chapter. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see References in Text note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s2101"},"text":"section 2101 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id05c265c8-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section reflects the ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 2021","children":[],"tail":", reversion to provisions in effect on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2014","children":[],"tail":". See Effective and Termination Dates of 2015 Revival note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/40/s233"},"text":"Section 233 of Pub. L. 112–40","children":[],"tail":", which provided for the "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2014","children":[],"tail":", revival of this section as in effect on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-02-13"},"text":"Feb. 13, 2011","children":[],"tail":", was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/27/tIV/s402/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–27, title IV, § 402(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2015-06-29"},"text":"June 29, 2015","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/129/374"},"text":"129 Stat. 374","children":[],"tail":", and the provisions of this section, as in effect on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2013-12-31"},"text":"Dec. 31, 2013","children":[],"tail":", were temporarily revived, effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2015-06-29"},"text":"June 29, 2015","children":[],"tail":", until "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 2021","children":[],"tail":", by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/27"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–27","children":[],"tail":", §§ 402(b), (c), 406. See 2011 and 2015 Amendment notes, Effective and Termination Dates of 2011 Revival notes, and Effective and Termination Dates of 2015 Revival notes below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/5/s1893"},"text":"Section 1893 of Pub. L. 111–5","children":[],"tail":", which provided for "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-02-13"},"text":"Feb. 13, 2011","children":[],"tail":", termination of amendment by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–5","children":[],"tail":", was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/40/tII/s201/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–40, title II, § 201(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 2011","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/125/403"},"text":"125 Stat. 403","children":[],"tail":", and the provisions of this section, as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–5","children":[],"tail":" and as in effect on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-02-12"},"text":"Feb. 12, 2011","children":[],"tail":", were temporarily revived, effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 2011","children":[],"tail":", until "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2014","children":[],"tail":", by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/40"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–40","children":[],"tail":", §§ 201(b), (c), 233. See 2009 and 2011 Amendment notes, Effective and Termination Dates of 2009 Amendment notes, and Effective and Termination Dates of 2011 Revival notes below."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id05c265c9-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2015—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/27"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–27","children":[],"tail":", §§ 402(b), (c), 406, temporarily revived the provisions of this section, as in effect on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2013-12-31"},"text":"Dec. 31, 2013","children":[],"tail":". See Codification note above and 2011 Amendment and Effective and Termination Dates of 2015 Revival notes below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2011—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/40"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–40","children":[],"tail":", §§ 201(b), (c), 233, temporarily revived the provisions of this section, as in effect on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-02-12"},"text":"Feb. 12, 2011","children":[],"tail":". See Codification note above and 2009 Amendment and Effective and Termination Dates of 2011 Revival notes below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2009—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–5","children":[],"tail":", §§ 1822(1)(A), (B), 1893, temporarily substituted “unemployment shall” for “total unemployment shall” and “subsections (b), (c), and (d)” for “subsections (b) and (c)” in introductory provisions. See Codification note above and Effective and Termination Dates of 2009 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–5","children":[],"tail":", §§ 1822(1)(C), 1893, temporarily inserted “, except that in the case of an adversely affected worker who is participating in training under this part, such income shall not include earnings from work for such week that are equal to or less than the most recent weekly benefit amount of the unemployment insurance payable to the worker for a week of total unemployment preceding the worker’s first exhaustion of unemployment insurance (as determined for purposes of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s2291/a/3/B"},"text":"section 2291(a)(3)(B) of this title","children":[],"tail":")” before period. See Codification note above and Effective and Termination Dates of 2009 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–5","children":[],"tail":", §§ 1822(2), 1893, temporarily added subsec. (d). See Codification note above and Effective and Termination Dates of 2009 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/418/s1423/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–418, § 1423(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “, including on-the-job training,” after “approved by the Secretary”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/418/s1423/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–418, § 1423(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “under section 2291(b)” for “under section 2291(c) or 2296(c)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/272"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–272","children":[],"tail":" substituted “under any Federal law other than this chapter” for “under any Federal law,”, “section 2291(c) or 2296(c) of this title” for “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s2296/c"},"text":"section 2296(c) of this title","children":[],"tail":"”, and “If such training allowance” for “If the training allowance”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1981—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/35/s2504/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–35, § 2504(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted provisions setting forth amount of allowance as reduced (but not below zero) by training allowance and income deductions for provisions setting forth amount of allowance as computed by specified percentages of wages and reduced by paid remuneration."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsecs. (c), (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/35/s2504/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–35, § 2504(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":"–(4), redesignated subsec. (d) as (c) and struck out references to unemployment insurance and to the inapplicability of former subsecs. (c) and (e) of this section. Former subsec. (c), which related to the computation of unemployment insurance, was struck out."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/35/s2504/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–35, § 2504(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", struck out subsec. (e) which related to maximum total for all remuneration and allowances."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/35/s2504/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–35, § 2504(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", struck out subsec. (f) which authorized rounding off to whole dollar amounts."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id05c4aeba-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":nul